content: It's really good and It helps you get to bed on time
It nice
It really helps whose want to construct a health habit of sleep.

I love the developer's other app Forest which I have found to be extremely helpful in maintaining focus and produgt6ctivity while I work, so I was excited to try this app out to help me get a regular sleep schedule, and it has! It motivates me to go to bed and wake up on time, using adorable little buildings in an adorable little town and daily income, which increases with every successful night's sleep (tbh in not sure what the gold is for other than building a new town). I'm a big fan. I only have minor criticisms. In the app, there is a really cool "Buildex" that shows all the buildings that are possible to build and reveals the ones you've completed; however, no information about the building is given other than the day you built it and how much revenue it generates. I would love to see a name for all buildings and maybe a little blurb about its function. It would make the app a lot more fun. Additionally, you can tap on some things that will bring up a small information bubble. These bubbles disappear so quickly that I'm unable to read it all with one tap, so I have to tap it 4 or 5 times to read it all. Lastly, after purchasing the premium version, I was unable to redeem my free building when I linked this account with my Forest account (I have the paid version for Forest as well). I think these three topics should be addressed, and they would really benefit the app. Overall, I'm happy I found this. Congrats on another successful productivity app! Edit: followed the developer's instructions in their reply and was able to redeem my Forest tree. Thank you!
replyContent:
Hello,

Please go to SleepTown's settings page and tap the cell with your user name on it. 

This will lead you to your profile page where you can find the redeem button for "special Forest house".  
On certain phone models, you might have to open Forest before claiming the "special Forest house" for it work properly.

Thanks for contacting us! :)
